#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.228"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.228:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.228:0.2"
msgid "23. Dīghacārikavagga"
msgstr "23. Long Wandering"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.228:0.3"
msgid "228. Ussūrabhattasutta"
msgstr "228. Eating Late"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.260"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.228:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā ussūrabhatte kule."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for a family who takes their "
"meals late in the day."

msgctxt "an5.228:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.228:1.3"
msgid "Ye te atithī pāhunā, te na kālena paṭipūjenti;"
msgstr "When guests visit, they are not served on time."

msgctxt "an5.228:1.4"
msgid "yā tā balipaṭiggāhikā devatā, tā na kālena paṭipūjenti;"
msgstr "The deities who accept spirit-offerings are not served on time."

msgctxt "an5.228:1.5"
msgid ""
"ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekabhattikā rattūparatā viratā vikālabhojanā, te na "
"kālena paṭipūjenti;"
msgstr ""
"Ascetics and brahmins who eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating "
"at night, and from food at the wrong time are not served on time."

# I can’t see any justification for BB’s vimukha= “grimace”. All the dicts say it means “avert”, Skt as well as Pali, and it is opposite to “abhimukha”. Comm. here says kammaṃ vissajjetvā nisīdanti
msgctxt "an5.228:1.6"
msgid "dāsakammakaraporisā vimukhā kammaṃ karonti;"
msgstr "Bondservants, workers, and staff do their duties neglectfully."

msgctxt "an5.228:1.7"
msgid "tāvatakaṃyeva asamayena bhuttaṃ anojavantaṃ hoti."
msgstr "A meal eaten during the wrong period is not nutritious."

msgctxt "an5.228:1.8"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā ussūrabhatte kule."
msgstr ""
"These are the five drawbacks for a family who takes their meals late in the "
"day."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.228:2.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā samayabhatte kule."
msgstr ""
"There are these five benefits for a family who takes their meals at a proper "
"time."

msgctxt "an5.228:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.228:2.3"
msgid "Ye te atithī pāhunā, te kālena paṭipūjenti;"
msgstr "When guests visit, they are served on time."

msgctxt "an5.228:2.4"
msgid "yā tā balipaṭiggāhikā devatā, tā kālena paṭipūjenti;"
msgstr "The deities who accept spirit-offerings are served on time."

msgctxt "an5.228:2.5"
msgid ""
"ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekabhattikā rattūparatā viratā vikālabhojanā, te kālena "
"paṭipūjenti;"
msgstr ""
"Ascetics and brahmins who eat in one part of the day, abstaining from eating "
"at night, and from food at the wrong time are served on time."

msgctxt "an5.228:2.6"
msgid "dāsakammakaraporisā avimukhā kammaṃ karonti;"
msgstr "Bondservants, workers, and staff do their duties attentively."

msgctxt "an5.228:2.7"
msgid "tāvatakaṃyeva samayena bhuttaṃ ojavantaṃ hoti."
msgstr "A meal eaten during the proper period is nutritious."

msgctxt "an5.228:2.8"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā samayabhatte kule”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the five benefits for a family who takes their meals at a proper "
"time.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.228:2.9"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
